	<section>
		<h2>What is Accountability Software?</h2>
		<p>
			Accountability software is designed for individuals who want help maintaining personal integrity online. Unlike parental control software that focuses on blocking, accountability software focuses on transparency‚Äîreporting activity to a trusted accountability partner. This approach is based on the principle that accountability, not just blocking, helps people make better choices.
		</p>

		<div class="alert alert-success">
			<strong>Best for:</strong> Adults, older teens, individuals seeking personal accountability, religious communities, recovering from addiction.
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>üÜö Accountability vs. Filtering Software</h2>

		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6">
			<div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h3 class="mt-0 mb-4 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400">Accountability Software</h3>
				<ul class="pl-5 m-0">
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Philosophy:</strong> Transparency and reporting</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Approach:</strong> Trust-based with visibility</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Blocking:</strong> Optional or minimal</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Reports to:</strong> Chosen accountability partner(s)</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Adults, voluntary use</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h3 class="mt-0 mb-4 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400">Parental Control Software</h3>
				<ul class="pl-5 m-0">
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Philosophy:</strong> Prevention and blocking</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Approach:</strong> Control-based</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Blocking:</strong> Primary feature</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Reports to:</strong> Parents/administrators</li>
					<li class="mb-2 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Children, mandatory use</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="alert alert-info">
			<strong>Key Difference:</strong> Accountability software assumes the user wants help and chooses accountability voluntarily. Filtering software assumes the user needs protection and may resist controls.
		</div>
	</section>

